## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/symbol">Symbol</a> representation.

Symbols represent locations within <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/addressable">Addressable</a> objects. They can be either Named or Anonymous. Anonymous symbols have neither linkage nor visibility, and must point at ContentBlocks. Named symbols may be in one of four states:
<ul>
<li>Null: Default initialized. Assignable, but otherwise unusable.</li>
<li>Defined: Has both linkage and visibility and points to a ContentBlock</li>
<li>Common: Has both linkage and visibility, points to a null <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/addressable">Addressable</a>.</li>
<li>External: Has neither linkage nor visibility, points to an external <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/addressable">Addressable</a>.</li>
</ul>

Definition at line 432 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/jitlink/jitlink-h">JITLink.h</a>.

### Symbol() {#a1c18f9ab46d326665b4df1640dbe09fe}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="llvm::jitlink::Symbol::Symbol ()"
  labels = {["default"]}>
Create a null <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitlink/symbol">Symbol</a>.

This allows Symbols to be default initialized for use in containers (e.g. as map values). Null symbols are only useful for assigning to.
